# Public vs private — MY20-PHEV/yakr

This repository is **public on GitHub**. Treat homelab, deploy, and operator material as **private by default**.

## Never commit or push without explicit user approval

- Real **IP addresses** (VPS, Tailscale, homelab, parking/registrar)
- **SSH users**, hostnames, tunnel/forwarding setup, Traefik/Docker network names tied to your homelab
- **Secrets**, `.env` files, wrap secrets, API keys, certificates
- **yakr.co.uk website** source and deploy (`website/`, `logos/`, `deploy/homelab-website/`, homelab website scripts/docs)
- **Operator runbooks** with real infrastructure values
- Anything under `.gitignore` paths for private/local use

## Already gitignored (keep local only)

See `.gitignore` sections for `homelab_tailscale.local.env`, `yakr-co-uk-deploy.local.md`, `website/`, `deploy/homelab-website/`, `scripts/homelab_website_*.sh`, etc.

Use `*.example` templates with placeholders (`100.x.x.x`, `your-ssh-user`) — never real values.

## Before git commit or push

1. Run `git diff --staged` and scan for IPs, `devos@`, Tailscale, VPS, homelab paths, deploy scripts.
2. If the change is **ops/infra/website/deploy** or you are **unsure** → **ask the user first**.
3. Do not push homelab scaffolding “for convenience” — local + gitignored is fine.

## Public repo may include

- Protocol spec, reference code, test vectors, certification docs
- Generic docs with **no** real infrastructure identifiers
- Links to **live public URLs** (e.g. `https://yakr.co.uk`) without exposing how they are hosted

## If sensitive data was pushed

- Do **not** only delete files in a follow-up commit (history retains them).
- Tell the user; use history rewrite (`git filter-repo`) and force-push only with their explicit approval.
- Mention forks/clones and GitHub object cache may still retain old data briefly.

## Examples

```
# ❌ BAD — real infra on public repo
HOMELAB_TAILSCALE_IP=100.125.109.114
ssh devos@100.125.109.114 'docker ps'
| yakr.co.uk A | 145.223.68.183 |

# ✅ GOOD — placeholders or gitignored local files
HOMELAB_TAILSCALE_IP=100.x.x.x
ssh <HOMELAB_SSH_USER>@<HOMELAB_TAILSCALE_IP> 'docker ps'
| yakr.co.uk A | <VPS_PUBLIC_IP> |
```
